      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 1:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the whole practical teaching of Christianity is called a “charge.” Here the Apostle is referring to particular items of conduct as matter of so many “charges.” These charges were given “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "through",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the Lord Jesus,” since His name and authority were used to support them (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Thessalonians 3:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ”); while they were given “",
        "children": []
